# Cartridge & Cast

Marketplace for booking fly fishing and wingshooting lodges worldwide. This monorepo contains the Python/FastAPI backend and the Next.js frontend.

```
jet_set/
├── app/            # FastAPI API, models, services, worker
├── acquire/        # CLI for prospect discovery & outreach
├── frontend/       # Next.js 16 frontend (App Router)
├── alembic/        # Database migrations
├── scripts/        # Seed & admin bootstrap scripts
├── tests/          # Backend test suite
├── docker-compose.yml
├── Dockerfile
└── pyproject.toml
```

---

## Prerequisites

| Tool | Version | Notes |
|------|---------|-------|
| **Python** | 3.11+ | Backend runtime |
| **Node.js** | 22+ | Frontend runtime (Next.js 16 requires >= 20.9) |
| **npm** | 10+ | Ships with Node 22 |
| **Docker** | Latest | For PostgreSQL (and optionally the full stack) |

### Installing Node 22 via nvm

If you don't have Node 22 installed:

```bash
# Install nvm if you don't have it
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.40.3/install.sh | bash

# Install and use Node 22
nvm install 22
nvm use 22
node --version  # should print v22.x.x
```

---

## Quick Start (Full Stack)

The fastest path to a running local environment:

```bash
# 1. Clone and enter
git clone <repo-url>
cd jet_set

# 2. Start Postgres
docker-compose up -d postgres

# 3. Backend setup
python3.11 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -e '.[dev]'
cp .env.example .env
alembic upgrade head
python scripts/seed_species.py
python scripts/seed_destinations.py

# 4. Start the API (terminal 1)
uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000

# 5. Frontend setup (terminal 2)
nvm use 22
cd frontend
cp .env.local.example .env.local
npm install
npm run dev

# 6. Open http://localhost:3000
```

The API runs at `http://localhost:8000` and the frontend at `http://localhost:3000`.

---

## Backend Setup (Detailed)

### 1. Create a Virtual Environment

```bash
python3.11 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
```

### 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -e '.[dev]'
```

If you're on zsh and see `no matches found: .[dev]`, quote the extras:

```bash
pip install -e '.[dev]'
```

### 3. Configure Environment

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Edit `.env` to set the database URL for Postgres:

```env
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/cartridge_cast
APP_ENV=local
```

You can leave all external service keys (`AUTH0_*`, `STRIPE_*`, `AWS_*`, `RESEND_API_KEY`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY`) blank for local development. The backend stubs these integrations when credentials are missing.

### 4. Start PostgreSQL

```bash
docker-compose up -d postgres
```

Verify it's running:

```bash
docker-compose ps
```

For a quick smoke test without Docker, you can use the default SQLite URL from `.env.example`, but all team development should use Postgres.

### 5. Run Migrations

```bash
alembic upgrade head
```

To reset the database:

```bash
docker-compose down -v
docker-compose up -d postgres
alembic upgrade head
```

### 6. Seed Reference Data

```bash
python scripts/seed_species.py
python scripts/seed_destinations.py
```

Optionally create an admin user:

```bash
python scripts/create_admin.py \
  --auth0-id 'auth0|local-admin' \
  --email admin@example.com \
  --name "Local Admin"
```

### 7. Start the API

```bash
uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000
```

Verify:

- Health check: http://localhost:8000/api/v1/health
- OpenAPI docs: http://localhost:8000/docs
- ReDoc: http://localhost:8000/redoc

### 8. Start the Worker (Optional)

The async job worker processes background tasks (booking reminders, etc.):

```bash
python -m app.worker
```

### 9. Local Auth for Protected Endpoints

When `APP_ENV` is not `production`, bypass Auth0 with the `X-Debug-User` header:

```bash
# As a sportsman
curl http://localhost:8000/api/v1/users/me \
  -H 'X-Debug-User: {"auth0_id":"auth0|dev-user","email":"user@example.com","name":"Dev User","role":"sportsman"}'

# As a lodge owner
curl http://localhost:8000/api/v1/users/me \
  -H 'X-Debug-User: {"auth0_id":"auth0|dev-owner","email":"owner@example.com","name":"Dev Owner","role":"lodge_owner"}'

# As an admin
curl http://localhost:8000/api/v1/users/me \
  -H 'X-Debug-User: {"auth0_id":"auth0|dev-admin","email":"admin@example.com","name":"Dev Admin","role":"admin"}'
```

### 10. Run Backend Tests

```bash
pytest
```

Or run specific suites:

```bash
pytest tests/services/test_booking_service.py
pytest tests/services/test_review_service.py
pytest tests/services/test_claim_service.py
pytest tests/api/test_health.py
```

---

## Frontend Setup (Detailed)

### 1. Switch to Node 22

```bash
nvm use 22
```

If Node 22 isn't installed yet: `nvm install 22`

### 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
```

### 3. Configure Environment

```bash
cp .env.local.example .env.local
```

The defaults work out of the box for local development:

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

Optional keys (leave blank until needed):

| Variable | When needed |
|----------|-------------|
| `AUTH0_SECRET`, `AUTH0_BASE_URL`, `AUTH0_ISSUER_BASE_URL`, `AUTH0_CLIENT_ID`, `AUTH0_CLIENT_SECRET` | When configuring real Auth0 login |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` | When testing Stripe checkout |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_KEY` | When enabling map components |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_CDN_DOMAIN` | When serving images from CloudFront |

### 4. Start the Dev Server

```bash
npm run dev
```

Open http://localhost:3000. The frontend proxies API calls to `http://localhost:8000`, so make sure the backend is running.

### 5. Build for Production

```bash
npm run build
npm start
```

### 6. Lint

```bash
npm run lint
```

---

## Frontend Architecture

### Tech Stack

| Layer | Choice |
|-------|--------|
| Framework | Next.js 16 (App Router) |
| Language | TypeScript (strict mode) |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui (base-ui) |
| Server state | TanStack Query (React Query) |
| Forms | React Hook Form + Zod |
| Auth | Auth0 Next.js SDK (stubbed for local dev) |
| Payments | Stripe.js + React Stripe Elements |
| Maps | Google Maps (placeholder, integration pending) |
| Calendar | react-day-picker (booking), FullCalendar (admin, pending) |
| Charts | Recharts (admin dashboard) |
| Fonts | Playfair Display (serif headlines) + DM Sans (body) |

### Route Groups

The app is organized into four route groups with isolated layouts and code splitting:

```
src/app/
├── (public)/     # SSR public pages — SEO-critical, no auth required
│   ├── /                        Homepage
│   ├── /lodges                  Search & browse lodges
│   ├── /lodges/[slug]           Lodge detail (JSON-LD, OG meta)
│   ├── /lodges/[slug]/claim     Claim your lodge flow
│   ├── /experiences/[id]        Experience detail + availability
│   ├── /destinations            Destination directory
│   ├── /destinations/[slug]     Destination landing page
│   ├── /species                 Species directory
│   ├── /species/[slug]          Species landing page
│   ├── /fly-fishing             Fly fishing vertical
│   ├── /wingshooting            Wingshooting vertical
│   └── /about                   About page
│
├── (auth)/       # Auth-required pages — dashboard & lodge admin
│   ├── /dashboard               Sportsman dashboard
│   ├── /dashboard/bookings      Booking list
│   ├── /dashboard/bookings/[id] Booking detail + cancel
│   ├── /dashboard/reviews/[id]  Write review form
│   ├── /dashboard/profile       Profile settings
│   ├── /lodge-admin             Lodge admin overview
│   ├── /lodge-admin/bookings    Incoming bookings
│   ├── /lodge-admin/payouts     Stripe Connect payouts
│   ├── /lodge-admin/lodges/[id] Lodge profile editor
│   └── /lodge-admin/lodges/[id]/availability  Availability manager
│
├── (admin)/      # Platform admin — metrics, approvals
│   ├── /admin                   KPI dashboard (Recharts)
│   ├── /admin/lodges            Lodge claim approvals
│   ├── /admin/prospects         Prospect pipeline
│   └── /admin/policies          Cancellation policies
│
└── api/          # Route handlers
    └── /api/auth/[...auth0]     Auth0 callback (stubbed)
```

### Key Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/lib/types.ts` | All TypeScript interfaces — mirrors backend Pydantic schemas exactly |
| `src/lib/api-client.ts` | Typed fetch wrapper for all 22 backend API endpoints |
| `src/lib/utils.ts` | `cn()`, `formatCents()`, `formatDate()`, `formatDateRange()` |
| `src/lib/constants.ts` | Sport types, sort options, route helpers, booking status labels |
| `src/hooks/` | 7 React Query hooks: lodges, experiences, bookings, reviews, availability, search, current-user |
| `src/providers/providers.tsx` | TanStack Query + TooltipProvider setup |
| `src/components/layout/` | Header, Footer, LodgeAdminSidebar |
| `src/components/lodge/` | LodgeCard, LodgeHero, LodgeInfo, LodgeReviews, ClaimBanner |
| `src/components/search/` | SearchBar, SearchFilters, SearchResults, SportTypeToggle |
| `src/components/booking/` | AvailabilityCalendar, BookingForm, BookingConfirmation |
| `src/components/review/` | ReviewCard, RatingBreakdown, RatingStars |

### shadcn/ui Notes

This project uses shadcn/ui v4 with **@base-ui/react** primitives (not Radix UI). Key differences from older shadcn:

- **No `asChild` prop** — Trigger components render their children directly
- Components are in `src/components/ui/` and can be customized freely
- Install new components with: `npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>`

### Adding a New Page

1. Create directory under the appropriate route group in `src/app/`
2. Add `page.tsx` — default export a React component
3. For dynamic routes, params is a Promise: `const { slug } = await params`
4. For data fetching in Server Components, use `fetch()` directly
5. For client-side data, use the hooks from `src/hooks/`
6. Add SEO metadata via `export const metadata` or `generateMetadata()`

---

## API Endpoints Reference

All endpoints are under `/api/v1`. Full docs at http://localhost:8000/docs when the backend is running.

### Public

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| GET | `/lodges` | List lodges (cursor pagination) |
| GET | `/lodges/{slug}` | Lodge detail |
| GET | `/lodges/{slug}/reviews` | Lodge reviews |
| GET | `/search/lodges` | Search lodges (filters, sorting) |
| GET | `/experiences/{id}/availability` | Experience availability windows |
| GET | `/species` | List all species |
| GET | `/destinations` | List all destinations |

### Authenticated (Sportsman)

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| POST | `/bookings` | Create booking (returns Stripe client_secret) |
| GET | `/bookings/me` | List my bookings |
| POST | `/bookings/{id}/cancel` | Cancel booking |
| POST | `/bookings/{id}/pay-balance` | Pay remaining balance |
| POST | `/reviews` | Submit review |
| GET | `/users/me` | Get current user |
| POST | `/lodges/{slug}/claim` | Claim a lodge |
| POST | `/uploads/presign` | Get S3 presigned upload URL |

### Lodge Admin (`lodge_owner` role)

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| POST | `/lodge-admin/availability` | Create availability windows |
| GET | `/lodge-admin/bookings` | List lodge's bookings |
| GET | `/lodge-admin/payouts` | Payout history |

### Platform Admin (`admin` role)

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| GET | `/admin/metrics` | Platform KPIs |
| POST | `/admin/claims/{id}/decision` | Approve/reject claims |
| GET | `/admin/cancellation-policies` | List policies |
| POST | `/admin/cancellation-policies` | Create policy |

### Key Conventions

- **Pagination**: Cursor-based — `{ items: T[], meta: { next_cursor: string | null } }`
- **Prices**: All in **cents** (integers). Divide by 100 for display.
- **IDs**: UUIDs everywhere
- **Lodge lookup**: by `slug` (public), by `id` (admin)
- **Auth**: `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>` or `X-Debug-User` header (local only)

---

## Acquire CLI

The `acquire` CLI discovers, scrapes, enriches, and manages outreach to prospective lodges:

```bash
acquire discover --region "bahamas" --sport fly_fishing
acquire scrape --batch --limit 10
acquire enrich --batch --limit 5
acquire outreach send --prospect-id <uuid> --template welcome
acquire prospects list --region bahamas
acquire prospects export --path prospects.csv
acquire stats
```

